        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 7:31PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 730 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Halfway, or 18 miles west of Arkadelphia, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hollywood...                      Lower Lake Recreation Area...
Halfway...                        Alpine...
Shawmut...                        Amity...
DeGray Lake State Park...         Caddo Valley...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CDT for
southwestern Arkansas.</instruction>
